// Một server xử lý 10,000 concurrent requests mà không tạo 10,000 threads!

http.createServer((req, res) => {

  db.query('SELECT * FROM users', (err, rows) => {

    res.end(JSON.stringify(rows));  // execute khi DB query xong

  });

  // Main thread tiếp tục ngay lập tức

}).listen(3000);

Node.js handles concurrency through an event-driven, non-blocking I/O model — without the need to create multiple threads.

- Event loop: Runs on the main thread, continuously listening for and processing events.

- Non-blocking I/O: When an I/O operation is encountered, Node.js delegates it to the OS/libuv and continues processing other requests.

- Callback queue: When I/O completes, the callback enters the queue → the event loop executes it when the call stack is free.

