A module is a reusable block of code that provides specific functionality. Node.js has 3 main types of modules:

- Built-in modules: http, fs, path, os, events, stream, crypto, dns, cluster — no installation needed.

- Third-party modules: Installed via npm — express, lodash, axios, mongoose...

- Custom modules: Written and exported by the developer.

