Control flow in Node.js is the management of the execution order of async operations. Because Node.js is non-blocking, tasks do not always complete in the order they were started.

- Callbacks: The traditional approach — prone to callback hell when deeply nested.

- Promises (.then/.catch): Chains async operations more cleanly, better error handling.

- async/await: Syntax closer to synchronous, most readable, but still async underneath.

