Streams process data in chunks instead of loading everything into memory — very efficient for large files, video, or real-time data.

- Readable — Read data in chunks. Example: fs.createReadStream(), http.IncomingMessage.

- Writable — Write data in chunks. Example: fs.createWriteStream(), http.ServerResponse.

- Duplex — Read and write simultaneously. Example: TCP socket (net.Socket).

- Transform — Transform data as it passes through. Example: zlib.createGzip(), crypto.createCipher().

