Callback hell is the situation where many callbacks are nested too deeply, creating a pyramid structure that is hard to read and maintain.

- Solution: Use async/await — syntax closest to synchronous, easiest to read and debug.

- Solution: Use Promises (.then/.catch) — chain async operations cleanly.

- Solution: Use named functions — avoid anonymous inline nesting.

